The panel provided allows modification of the properties of the chosen datasection or attribute. Select the datasection or attribute in the **Data Schema **panel to display the relative properties.

## **Data section properties**
**![](data:image/png;base64,)**

**Properties**

**Description**

**Datasection Name**

Display the datasection name in the XML file.

**Datasection Label**

Set a label that will be displayed in the data schema next to the name of the datasection. This label will be shown in all the uses of the attribute in the rest of the user application

**Record Usage in print**

Select one or more data sections that you wish to trace throughout the generation of the document. To do so, select the **Record usage in print **checkbox. Next to the corresponding data section, in the tree view, a red target icon will appear indicating that the data section is set for being traced.

# Attribute properties
![](data:image/png;base64,)

**Properties**

**Description**

**Attribute name**

Display the attribute name in the XML file.

**Attribute label**

Set a label that will be displayed in the data schema next to the name of the attribute. This label will be shown in all the uses of the attribute in the rest of the user application.

**Custom attribute styles**

Allow the creation of new attribute styles.

**Value restrictions**

Allow restrictions to be placed on the values to be assigned to string-type attributes.

### **Adding custom attribute styles**
Each attribute has a preset style which will decide the appearance of the corresponding variable data inserted in the document during print spool generation. It is possible to create additional styles and assign them to the attributes using the relevant panel. The panel will show the properties of the type of attribute selected.

![](data:image/png;base64,)

#### String attribute style
![](data:image/png;base64,)

**Properties**

**Description**

**Use format**

Enable/disable the use of a different format for the value of the attribute.

**Previous text**

Insert a text before the body of the attribute text.

**Next text**

Insert a text after the body of the attribute text.

**Number of characters**

Set the maximum number of characters for the attribute.

**Offset from start**

Set the offset with respect to the the start of the original value. The characters before the start point will not be present in the style value.

**Upper case/ Lower case**

Select the string format.

> Warning

If the maximum number of characters set for the style is less than the length of the value of the attribute supplied during print spool generation, the value is cut off.

#### Date attribute style
![](data:image/png;base64,)

**Properties**

**Description**

**Use format**

Enable/disable the use of a different format for the value of the attribute.

**Previous text**

Insert a text before the body of the attribute text.

**Next text**

Insert a text after the body of the attribute text.

**Date pattern**

Select the date pattern.

#### Numerical attribute style
![](data:image/png;base64,)

Properties

Description

**Use format**

Enable/disable the use of a different format for the value of the attribute.

**Previous text**

Insert a text before the body of the attribute text.

**Next text**

Insert a text after the body of the attribute text.

**Group separator**

Set the symbol used to separate thousands.

**Integers**

Set the number of integers digits.

**Decimals separator**

Set a symbol to be used for the decimals separator.

**Decimals**

Set the number of decimal digits.

**Zero padding**

Activate/deactivate zero padding with zeros on the right until the stated number of decimal digits is reached.

**Maximum number**

Display the maximum number which can be shown by the attribute.

**Financial formatting**

Allow to format numbers aligning them to the right, using the maximum number of digits allowed as a guide.

A space is inserted before positive numbers, mirroring the horizontal space required by the minus sign, in order to align the digits in columns containing both positive and negative numbers.

**Negative values in brackets**

Enable the use of brackets for negative numbers.

If the option is used together with financial formatting, it also requires the insertion of a space to the right of the positive numbers, to allow the alignment of numbers in columns. In this case, two spaces are inserted for positive numbers: one before (to account for the minus sign) and one after (to account for the bracket).

> Warning

If the number of decimal digits set for the style is less than the length of the value of the attribute supplied during print spool generation, the digits are cut off starting from the right. The same applies to whole digits, cut off starting from the left.

### Restricting attribute values
Value restriction involves the creation of a list of values which can be used for a given string type attribute.

When the attribute is used for rules, if a list of restrictions is present it is only possible to select the values in the list instead of any value of the user's choice.

![](data:image/png;base64,)

#### Creating a new value
- Select the attribute.

- Click the **New Value **button. An input box will be displayed.

- Enter the name of the value required in the input box.

![](data:image/png;base64,) 

#### Renaming a value
- Click the value you wish to rename.

- Enter the new name.

#### Removing a value
Click the **Remove **button of the value you wish to delete.
